'''J. C. Ramaswamy''' (c. 1928 â€“ 2 August 1986),{{cn|date=January 2019}} known by his [[Stage name|screen name]] '''Shakti Prasad''', was an Indian actor who appeared in [[Cinema of Karnataka|Kannada films]] in mostly villainous roles. In a career spanning close to 20 years, he appeared in over 200 films including landmark films such as ''[[Immadi Pulikeshi (film)|Immadi Pulikeshi]]'' (1967) and ''[[Antha (film)|Antha]]'' (1981).

He is the father of actor [[Arjun Sarja]] and grandfather of actors [[Chiranjeevi Sarja]], [[Dhruva Sarja]] and [[Aishwarya Arjun]].<ref>{{cite web |title= Arjun nephew in 'Vaayuputra' |url= http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/kannada/article/34897.html |publisher= ''indiaglitz.com'' |date= 26 November 2007 |accessdate= 6 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title= I am confident to make films in 1 to 20 crore: Arjun Sarja |url= http://chitratara.com/show-content.php?id=837&ptype=News&title=I%20AM%20CONFIDENT%20TO%20MAKE%20FILM%20IN%201%20TO%2020%20CRORES%20?%20ARJUN%20SARJA |publisher= ''chitratara.com'' |date= 25 May 2009 |accessdate= 5 November 2014}}</ref>

